{"id": "EUVD-2025-32272", "enisaUuid": "04ebab18-7279-3edd-88eb-63eb5e876e50", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnilfs2: fix potential UAF of struct nilfs_sc_info in nilfs_segctor_thread()\n\nThe finalization of nilfs_segctor_thread() can race with\nnilfs_segctor_kill_thread() which terminates that thread, potentially\ncausing a use-after-free BUG as KASAN detected.\n\nAt the end of nilfs_segctor_thread(), it assigns NULL to \"sc_task\" member\nof \"struct nilfs_sc_info\" to indicate the thread has finished, and then\nnotifies nilfs_segctor_kill_thread() of this using waitqueue\n\"sc_wait_task\" on the struct nilfs_sc_info.\n\nHowever, here, immediately after the NULL assignment to \"sc_task\", it is\npossible that nilfs_segctor_kill_thread() will detect it and return to\ncontinue the deallocation, freeing the nilfs_sc_info structure before the\nthread does the notification.\n\nThis fixes the issue by protecting the NULL assignment to \"sc_task\" and\nits notification, with spinlock \"sc_state_lock\" of the struct\nnilfs_sc_info.  Since nilfs_segctor_kill_thread() does a final check to\nsee if \"sc_task\" is NULL with \"sc_state_lock\" locked, this can eliminate\nthe race.", "datePublished": "2025-10-04T15:44:17", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-04T15:44:17", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53608", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/034cce77d52ba013ce62b4f5258c29907eb1ada5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0dbf0e64b91ee8fcb278aea93eb06fc7d56ecbcc", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/613bf23c070d11c525268f2945aa594704a9b764", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6be49d100c22ffea3287a4b19d7639d259888e33", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/92684e02654c91a61a0b0561433b710bcece19fe", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b4d80bd6370b81a1725b6b8f7894802c23a14e9f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bae009a2f1b7c2011d2e92d8c84868d315c0b97e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f32297dba338dc06d62286dedb3cdbd5175b1719"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53608", "GHSA-g3qq-fg79-63v4"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3103f40c-95a2-3c50-ad25-a8cfb043ef3f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.14.313"}, {"id": "31bfb6a0-1db9-3f28-b827-e7748c0e5773", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <613bf23c070d11c525268f2945aa594704a9b764"}, {"id": "4097fb2d-1935-3c1c-bf09-d66df16006a9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.24"}, {"id": "44742205-1c53-335c-98b4-83aca0c91395", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <b4d80bd6370b81a1725b6b8f7894802c23a14e9f"}, {"id": "5aaae18c-bc06-3198-9361-2bd6cda8a909", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <92684e02654c91a61a0b0561433b710bcece19fe"}, {"id": "7262ab04-fafc-3b0d-830a-70e19b4a4b11", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.19.281"}, {"id": "95faeae0-fca8-3ea8-b063-1798eede7918", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3"}, {"id": "9a366cd4-4b85-3884-9d1a-b5bb49963d2e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <0dbf0e64b91ee8fcb278aea93eb06fc7d56ecbcc"}, {"id": "ae8a9790-f039-3fde-8f1b-3fdc7a6f4145", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <034cce77d52ba013ce62b4f5258c29907eb1ada5"}, {"id": "af7902e4-f828-3821-8993-c958be438ccf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <6be49d100c22ffea3287a4b19d7639d259888e33"}, {"id": "bbfa1a86-db4b-3c9d-aec2-803efe509c21", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.107"}, {"id": "c1c01caa-e371-3dd6-a306-936347fd6057", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.241"}, {"id": "c3d9033b-d121-3fa3-a6f7-0abd89512174", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_ve